                <h1>"Exploring Irony in 'The Yellow Wallpaper'"</h1>
                <p>In "The Yellow Wallpaper," irony permeates the narrative, highlighting the protagonist's struggle against patriarchal oppression. As the narrator's mental state deteriorates, the wallpaper transforms from a mere decoration to a symbol of entrapment. The irony lies in her husband's belief that isolation will cure her while it only exacerbates her condition, showcasing the detrimental effects of misguided concern.</p>
